                    </div>
                    <span>This book is a continuation of the first book, "Rich Dad, Poor Dad." Some of the material is repetitive. This is not a problem as it goes deeper into cash flow concepts. The book does not give any simple answers and does not give the reader a blueprint or recipe to success. However, the book is superb at assisting the reader in thinking about money in a healthy way. The reader is given the concept in having money work for the reader, rather than just working for money. You can work hard to put money to work rather than just working to get money to spend on wasting assets.</span>
                  
